Chelicera. Chelicera as in Muma (1970, p. 13, fig. 1–2) . VDC proximally located ( Fig. 1C ). Neither Roewer (1934) nor Muma (1970) mentioned or illustrated this unique position of the VDC. Fixed finger with no median dentition. Movable finger: large MP-three MSM attached to MP; distinct MPL (
Figs. 2I & J
). Fondal notch narrow, longer than wide (
Fig. 2I
). Two tiny RFA; fondal teeth I, III, II, IV prolaterally and retrolaterally ( Fig. 3C ).

Setation.
Dorsal setal complex typical tubular; 
pvd
extend to top of fondal tooth I; 
mpd
a proximal patch. A few, tiny, scattered bacilli on coxa of LI. Pedipalps with scattered, long, thin setae, and shorter, thicker setae. Palpal tibia with a series of strong setae basally on the mesal surface. No visible paired setae.
